HEADWORD: Jungermannia
<hw>Jun`ger*man"ni*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Jungermanni⟦ae⟧</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[NL. Named after <person>Ludwig <etsep>Jungermann</etsep></person>,
a German botanist.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of hepatic
mosses, now much circumscribed, but formerly comprising most plants of
the family, which is sometimes therefore called
<fam>Jungermanniace⟦ae⟧</fam>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

